\f0\b\fs66 \cf0 Chocolate-Hazelnut Gelato\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl320\ql\qnatural

\fs40 \cf2 Yield:  \cf0 6 to 8 servings (about 4 cups)\
\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl420\sa240\ql\qnatural

\fs52 \cf0 INGREDIENTS\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl260\sa280\ql\qnatural
\ls1\ilvl0
\b0\fs48 \cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}2 cups whole milk\
{\listtext	\'95	}1 cup heavy cream\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup sugar, plus 1/4 cup\
{\listtext	\'95	}4 egg yolks\
\pard\tx220\tx720\pardeftab720\li720\fi-720\sl260\sa280\ql\qnatural
\ls2\ilvl0\cf0 {\listtext	\'95	}1/2 teaspoon vanilla extract\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup chocolate-hazelnut spread (recommended: Nutella)\
{\listtext	\'95	}1/2 cup toasted hazelnuts, crushed, for garnish\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl440\sa280\ql\qnatural

\b\fs54 \cf3 DIRECTIONS\
\pard\pardeftab720\sl440\ql\qnatural

\b0\fs48 \cf3 In a saucepan combine the {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/milk/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 milk}}, cream, and 1/2 cup sugar over medium heat. Cook until the sugar dissolves, about 5 minutes.\
Meanwhile, in a medium bowl {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/whip/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 whip}} the egg yolks with the remaining sugar using an electric mixer until the eggs have become thick and pale yellow, about 4 minutes. Pour 1/2 cup of the warm milk and cream mixture into the egg mixture and stir. Add this mixture back into the saucepan. Cook over very low heat, stirring constantly, until the mixture becomes thick enough to coat the back of a wooden spoon, about 7 to 10 minutes.\
Place a strainer over a medium bowl and pour the warm {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/custard/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 custard}} mixture through the strainer. Stir in the vanilla and hazelnut spread until it dissolves. Chill mixture completely before pouring into an {\field{\*\fldinst{HYPERLINK "http://www.foodterms.com/encyclopedia/ice-cream/index.html"}}{\fldrslt \cf4 ice cream}} maker and follow manufacturer's instructions to freeze. }